<br>
I am going to have to agree with Vampriss about the mezmerize &quot;fix.&quot; This is one of the difficult parts of the class to master, and essentially why there are few good necromancers and magicians around. A pet is basically a controllable tank, and its ability to break mez is no different than a player. Controlling this <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> was</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> an art, and something to be proud of. While I can see this making things easier in general, it is a &quot;dumbing down&quot; for us. I believe firmly you should still be able to break mezmerize spells if you want to, but just have the pet back off when the spell lands if it is already fighting a mob.<br>
<br>
I think this is going to make the Pet Discipline ability significantly less useful. One of my goals before this was to reach Master, and obtain the skill, so that I would not have to use pet control to /pet hold. Now, the reasoning for the skill is greatly reduced, and it will probably move down on my list. This is sad - that was one of the few skills I actually deemed quite useful. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140815>Shiloch Venzolmes</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/utryunn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tryunn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.spazzmania.com/Ohtrux/A.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight</span><br>  Posts: 576<br> <font color=#00F500>(6/4/02 9:19:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub78.ezboard.com/fwalkersofvazaellefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=809.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.spazzmania.com/Ohtrux/EQsigs/subgen%5b1%5d.gif height=91 width=73></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pet Owners Rejoice!</span><hr size=1> I can understand why you guys feel the way you do about necro and mage pets. I hate when I'm grouped with someone who can't control their pet. But as Vamp said, this is mainly for us Enchanters. You'd be surprised to find out how many folks just don't understand that we CAN'T control our pets. They don't have the strength or stamina that necro pets have, and they don't have the root/stun/ds abilities of mage pets. They have taunt. That's it. And they're not really too good at that to be honest!  <p><center>
